comments: Garland (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Conley (UTA) on the perimeter.
Gobert (UTA) briefly grasps Allen's (CLE) arm and marginal contact occurs as he releases toward the rebound.
Allen (CLE) makes marginal contact with Gobert's (UTA) arm, which does not affect his made dunk.
Garland (CLE) pivots on the perimeter and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Mitchell (UTA), which causes him to lose his balance and stumble into the legal pick by Allen (CLE).
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Garland's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Conley (UTA) does not overtly or abruptly veer into Garland (CLE) and any contact is deemed marginal as they come together during the drive.

Allen (CLE) makes contact with Conley?s (UTA) arm, causing him to lose control of the ball when he tries to gather, and the ball goes out of bounds off of Conley. A defensive foul should have been called on Allen, but no foul was called and the play was incorrectly ruled out of bounds off of CLE.

Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in Markkanen's (CLE) path and has his arms slightly extended out when Markkanen initiates the marginal contact by grasping Gobert's arm as they disengage on the screen. The reaction by Markkanen is not commensurate with the level of contact.
O'Neale (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position on Garland (CLE) during the drive.
Gobert (UTA) places a resting hand on Garland (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as he brushes his arm before cleanly blocking the driving shot attempt.
Mitchell's (UTA) foot comes down out of bounds prior to releasing his pass back in bounds.
Allen (CLE) engages with O'Neale (UTA) during the rebound and the contact is marginal as it does not affect O'Neale's ability to secure the rebound.
Prior to the clean block by Mobley (CLE), Garland (CLE) extends his arm out and makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Conley (UTA) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Rubio's (CLE) chest during his transition play up the court.
Gobert (UTA) is in the paint and actively guarding an opponent within three seconds.
Allen (CLE) briefly grasps and immediately releases Gobert's (UTA) arm and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his ability to pursue the rebound.
Mobley (CLE) never has control of the ball and incidental contact occurs with his arm as O'Neale (UTA) and Gobert (UTA) pursue the rebound.
